You need to provide a special username and other parameters related to a specific host towhich you connect using SSH. To which file should you add this information?
A)  ~/.ssh/hosts
B)  ~/.ssh/known_hosts
C)  ~/.ssh/config
D)  ~/.ssh/hostconfig
C
C. The file ~/.ssh/config is the appropriate location for this type of configurationinformation. Of the other answers, only ~/.ssh/known_hosts exists and containspublic key information for hosts to which you have connected.
